Capitol Bancorp said it has sold its 80pct interest in CAP Mortgage Co Inc for 3.1 mln dlrs, addingthis is expected to result in an after tax gain of about900,000 dlrs to be reported in the first quarter.    Capitol Bancorp said the CAP Mortgage interest was sold toMichael M. Bronstein, president of CAP Mortgage, and RobertFox, president of Fox Properties Inc. Bronstein already heldthe other 20 pct of CAP Mortgage's stock. Reuter&#3;